# Project Environment

Development machine:

- macOS
- Cursor IDE
- Node.js 22.22.3 (nvm)
- Python 3.14
- PostgreSQL 17 (running locally)
- Redis 8 (running locally)
- Docker (OrbStack)
- Ollama 0.30.8 (http://localhost:11434)
- Firebase CLI installed
- Vercel CLI installed
- Git installed

Backend stack:

- FastAPI
- SQLAlchemy 2.x (async)
- PostgreSQL 17
- Redis 8
- Alembic (dependency in `pyproject.toml`)
- Docker

Rules:

- Use PostgreSQL as the primary database (`DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://…`).
- Use Redis for caching and background jobs (`REDIS_URL`).
- Prefer Docker containers for local services (OrbStack).
- Use Ollama for local AI inference when possible; OpenAI/Gemini only when keys are set.
- Do not suggest MongoDB, Kafka, Kubernetes, or Terraform unless explicitly requested.
- Generate production-grade code.
- Use environment variables from `.env`.
- Use async FastAPI patterns when appropriate.
- Extend existing modules — do not introduce parallel stacks for the same concern.

