# Platform stack registry (pillar × capability × agent)
- Backend: `app/platform/stack_registry.py`, probes: `app/platform/stack_probe.py`
- API: `GET /api/v1/platform/stack/matrix|health|section/{id}|agents/routing`
- Frontend mirror: `_ai-share/synth-1-full/src/lib/platform-stack-integration.ts`
- Agent routing: `app/agents/stack_routing.py` (orchestrator reads `pillar`, `role`, `section_id` in context)

## Platform Core pillars × stack (summary)

| Pillar | RU title | Primary stack capabilities |
|--------|----------|----------------------------|
| `development` | ТЗ → образец | PostgreSQL, SQLAlchemy, Alembic, catalog, image upload, AI |
| `sample_collection` | Образец → коллекция | PostgreSQL, catalog, image upload, AI |
| `collection_order` | Коллекция → заказ | PostgreSQL, catalog, payments (Stripe/ЮKassa), AI |
| `order_production` | Заказ → производство | PostgreSQL, SQLAlchemy, Alembic |
| `comms` | Связь | JWT, users, Firebase Auth |

**Roles:** `brand`, `shop`, `manufacturer`, `supplier` — see `platform-core-hub-matrix.ts`.

**Horizontal (all roles):** auth/users via JWT; PG as SoT; AI agents via `app/agents/` + Ollama.

---

## 1. PostgreSQL

- Engine/session: `app/db/session.py`
- Models: `app/db/models/` (e.g. `core.py`, `product.py`)
- Local: PostgreSQL 17; Platform Core / Workshop2 PG: `docker-compose.workshop2.yml` (port **5433**)
- Env: `DATABASE_URL` in `.env` (prefer `postgresql+asyncpg://…`, not SQLite in new work)

## 2. SQLAlchemy

- Async sessions via `app/api/deps.py` → `get_db()`
- Repository pattern: `app/db/repositories/`
- Base model: `app/db/models/base.py`
- Prefer `Mapped[]` / SQLAlchemy 2.0 style already used in models

## 3. Alembic (migrations)

- Package: `alembic` in `pyproject.toml`
- Existing Python migration scripts: `app/db/migrations/` (see `app/db/migrations/README.md`)
- Frontend / Platform Core SQL: `_ai-share/synth-1-full/db/migrations/`
- **New schema changes:** prefer Alembic revisions; until `alembic/` is bootstrapped, follow existing `app/db/migrations/` or `_ai-share/synth-1-full/db/migrations/` patterns — do not add ad-hoc DDL in route handlers

## 4. JWT authorization

- Token create/verify: `app/core/security.py` (`create_access_token`, `ALGORITHM = HS256`)
- OAuth2 bearer + `get_current_user`: `app/api/deps.py`
- Login endpoint: `app/api/v1/endpoints/auth.py`
- Env: `SECRET_KEY`, `ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES`
- Do not add a second JWT library or parallel auth middleware

## 5. Users

- Model: `app/db/models/core.py` → `User`, `Organization`
- Schemas: `app/api/schemas/user.py`
- Roles enum: `app/api/deps.py` → `UserRole`
- Auth routes: `app/api/v1/endpoints/auth.py`

## 6. Product catalog

- Backend API: `app/api/v1/endpoints/product.py`, repositories in `app/db/repositories/product.py`
- Product/SKU models: `app/db/models/product.py`, `app/db/models/base.py`
- B2B catalog (frontend BFF): `_ai-share/synth-1-full/src/app/api/b2b/`, `src/lib/b2b/integrations/catalog-summary-source.ts`
- Marketplace sync base: `app/integrations/marketplace/base.py`
- Extend existing PIM/product routes — do not create a separate catalog service

## 7. Image / file upload

- DAM assets: `app/api/v1/endpoints/dam.py` + `app/services/dam_service.py`
- Bulk ingestion: `app/api/v1/endpoints/ingestion.py` (`UploadFile`)
- AI visual search by upload: `app/api/v1/endpoints/ai_routes.py`
- PLM documents: `app/api/v1/endpoints/plm/routes.py`
- W2 tech pack (S3 presign): `_ai-share/synth-1-full/docs/W2_TECHPACK_PILOT.md`
- Prefer existing DAM/ingestion endpoints; use Firebase Storage only on the frontend when Firebase is enabled

## 8. Firebase Auth

- Frontend only (canonical Next.js tree): `_ai-share/synth-1-full/src/lib/firebase/config.ts`, `firebase-env.ts`
- Lazy init; mock mode when keys missing; PG-only mode skips Firebase (`isWorkshop2PgOnlyMode`)
- Env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_*` in full app `.env`
- Backend auth stays JWT/FastAPI — do not duplicate user store in Firestore unless explicitly scoped

## 9. Stripe / ЮKassa (payments)

- **ЮKassa (RU):** stub + probes in `_ai-share/synth-1-full/src/lib/production/workshop2-yukassa-stub.ts`, routes under `_ai-share/synth-1-full/src/app/api/integrations/payments/yukassa/`
- Env (full): `YUKASSA_SHOP_ID`, `YUKASSA_SECRET_KEY`
- Backend payment config (Tinkoff/SBP): `app/core/config.py` → `PAYMENT_PROVIDER`, `TINKOFF_*`, `SBP_MERCHANT_ID`
- **Stripe:** not implemented yet — add via existing integrations pattern under `_ai-share/synth-1-full/src/app/api/integrations/payments/` (mirror YuKassa stub/probe layout); international cards → Stripe, RU market → ЮKassa
- Never hardcode payment secrets; gate with env and stub when keys absent

## 10. AI module (OpenAI / Ollama)

- Entry: `app/ai/llm_client.py`, router: `app/ai/llm_router.py`, config: `app/ai/ai_config.py`
- HTTP routes: `app/api/v1/endpoints/ai_routes.py`
- Embeddings / visual search: `app/ai/embeddings_search.py`, `app/ai/services/visual_similarity_service.py`
- Agents: `app/agents/`
- **Local (preferred):** Ollama at `http://localhost:11434` — models: `qwen3`, `llama3.3`, `deepseek-r1`
- **Cloud fallback:** `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY` / `AI_MODEL` in `app/core/config.py`
- Extend `LLMClient` for Ollama/OpenAI — do not add a second AI client abstraction

